# Project Guidelines for Claude Code

## File Editing Rules
- Always read entire files before editing
- Use 4 spaces for Python indentation
- Match exact whitespace and formatting
- If edit fails, re-read file and try again
- Show planned changes before applying

## Project Preferences
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Never create documentation files unless explicitly requested
- Keep responses concise and direct
- Use TodoWrite tool for complex multi-step tasks

## Code Style
- Follow existing code conventions in the project
- No comments unless explicitly requested
- Match library and framework choices used in codebase
- Security best practices always

## Chinese Language Support
- Support Chinese text and comments when present in codebase
- Maintain existing language patterns in files